reviews.review_text:
This is fun 5 stars for sound On the night of this show I know we were all pretty much disappointed. Now 29 years later this one is raw and raunchy. I Like the sound affects and the tempo its slow and spooky. Sound affects on Looks Like Rain also which rather common for the time frame. 
 2nd set is to me the local garage band playing for there friends.Touch of Grey's off a bit but still fun. Am listening to long Playing in the band now

Wow The BCT was a phenomenal venue, intimate and not a bad seat in the house.  Like HJK, had that chill Bay Area vibe where everything could really come together.  But sometimes the energy at these shows was zapped, maybe too short of a limo ride to and from home and too many, ahem, distractions.  Jerry sounds terrible and out of it, the rest of the band not much better.  A real clunker 0/1 star performance.  BUT the sound quality is awesome, so how about an average of 2.5 generously rounded up to 3?
